Accounts and Analytic Accounts Restrictions

Use this module to restrict who can access the Accounts from the Chart of Accounts and the Analytic Accounts across the whole system.

Features:

  1. Control who will have full access to the Accounts and Analytic Accounts.
  2. Control who will have restricted access to the Accounts and Analytic Accounts.
  3. Control the access per account and analytic account.
  4. The restrictions are applied to the COA and Analytic Accounts menus.
  5. The user will see only his allowed accounts on the Chart of Accounts, and his allowed Analytic Accounts (if he has access to the menus).
  6. The restricted user will be able to see and use only his allowed Accounts and Analytic Accounts on Journal Entries, Bills, Invoices, Cash & Bank transactions...
  7. Multi Companies restriction.

Activation:

  1. The users who will have restricted access will be added to the groups (Restrict Accounts) and/or (Restrict Analytic Accounts).
  2. Users with full access shouldn't be added to the Restriction groups.
  3. The restricted users must be added to the Allowed Users tab in Accounts and/or Analytic Account, so they can see and use them.

Example:

  1. Out of 43 Accounts, the restricted user "Accountant" sees only his allowed 11 accounts.
  2. Out of 18 Analytic Accounts, the restricted user "Accountant" sees only his allowed 2 analytic accounts.
